WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Created by ©Yozuki  |  #VisitUs  t.me/Yozukilk

2
00:00:01.720 --> 00:00:04.980
Why don't we get married?

3
00:00:06.370 --> 00:00:07.240
Huh?

4
00:00:07.520 --> 00:00:10.700
I don't mean a real marriage. Just pretend.

5
00:00:10.700 --> 00:00:11.650
Pretend?

6
00:00:11.650 --> 00:00:12.830
That's right.

7
00:00:12.830 --> 00:00:17.370
Kurokawa-san was saying unmarried 
people will be prioritized.

8
00:00:17.780 --> 00:00:21.130
So if we were to make it so we're married...

9
00:00:21.130 --> 00:00:25.070
Well, I'm on board with trying it.

10
00:00:25.070 --> 00:00:26.510
The fake marriage.

11
00:00:26.920 --> 00:00:29.330
Congratulations!

12
00:00:30.890 --> 00:00:32.140
<i>A surprise party?</i>

13
00:00:32.140 --> 00:00:34.900
H-How about these words?

14
00:00:34.900 --> 00:00:36.140
Y-Yes?

15
00:00:37.600 --> 00:00:38.430
P—

16
00:00:38.430 --> 00:00:40.690
Please marry me.

17
00:00:43.410 --> 00:00:47.870
Ohara-kun, please take your time 
thinking of a proposal.

18
00:00:48.620 --> 00:00:52.070
I'll wait as long as it takes.

19
00:00:57.550 --> 00:00:58.740
All right.

20
00:02:30.500 --> 00:02:35.010
What Does It Mean to Get Married?

21
00:02:37.930 --> 00:02:41.680
Kama, settle down.

22
00:02:42.310 --> 00:02:45.590
<i>Since yesterday, Kama 
won't leave my shirt alone.</i>

23
00:02:45.900 --> 00:02:49.840
<i>Maybe Honjoji-san's scent got on there.</i>

24
00:02:52.180 --> 00:02:55.820
<i>Wonder if I should put on the wedding ring.</i>

25
00:02:56.560 --> 00:02:58.820
<i>Why wasn't I able to say anything?</i>

26
00:02:59.140 --> 00:03:01.620
<i>Pretty pathetic, for a fake proposal.</i>

27
00:03:02.320 --> 00:03:04.970
<i>It was like I had a lump in my throat.</i>

28
00:03:04.970 --> 00:03:06.990
<i>What with someone that close,</i>

29
00:03:08.350 --> 00:03:10.170
<i>gazing at me.</i>

30
00:03:34.040 --> 00:03:35.800
I can't do it.

31
00:03:50.200 --> 00:03:52.180
Wow!

32
00:03:52.180 --> 00:03:54.920
What a long beach! It even has dunes!

33
00:03:54.920 --> 00:03:57.980
It's not white sands and 
green pines, but it's nice.

34
00:03:57.980 --> 00:04:01.100
It took three and a half hours, 
but I'm glad I came!

35
00:04:03.100 --> 00:04:05.740
Look at those big wind turbines turning.

36
00:04:05.740 --> 00:04:06.850
The power of nature is amazing!

37
00:04:06.850 --> 00:04:08.480
I'll say!

38
00:04:08.480 --> 00:04:11.360
<i>Whoops, I got a little carried away.</i>

39
00:04:12.390 --> 00:04:15.580
<i>Too many special events have happened lately.</i>

40
00:04:15.580 --> 00:04:19.530
<i>The party, crowds, the Ferris wheel, singing.</i>

41
00:04:19.530 --> 00:04:20.860
<i>It's stifling.</i>

42
00:04:21.760 --> 00:04:26.730
<i>I look at coastlines and collect
maps, stones, and sand.</i>

43
00:04:26.730 --> 00:04:29.250
<i>Those are the sorts of things I love.</i>

44
00:04:30.620 --> 00:04:35.070
<i>Marriage is so dazzling, 
the idea is downright exhausting.</i>

45
00:04:35.070 --> 00:04:37.130
<i>Even if it is fake.</i>

46
00:04:39.340 --> 00:04:42.420
Today, I'm going to enjoy some terrain.

47
00:04:44.260 --> 00:04:47.270
Ritsu

48
00:04:44.260 --> 00:04:47.270
I've gone to Tokyo today.

49
00:04:44.260 --> 00:04:47.270
How are you doing, Rika-san?

50
00:05:06.240 --> 00:05:09.750
Tokyo, you say? I'm not in Tokyo right now,
 but enjoy the city.

51
00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:14.770
<i>Leave me alone.</i>

52
00:05:25.880 --> 00:05:29.430
It was like an ordinary life.

53
00:05:29.820 --> 00:05:32.240
<i>I'm too irresponsible.</i>

54
00:05:32.580 --> 00:05:34.940
<i>Am I going to sit here forever 
and do nothing?</i>

55
00:05:35.230 --> 00:05:37.110
<i>How old am I, again?</i>

56
00:05:37.110 --> 00:05:39.300
<i>Is this how an adult acts?</i>

57
00:05:47.800 --> 00:05:49.200
<i>H-Huh?</i>

58
00:05:50.110 --> 00:05:53.420
<i>I put the ring on, and 
suddenly, my doubts are gone.</i>

59
00:05:58.650 --> 00:06:02.570
<i>It's weird. Right now I feel 
like I could do anything.</i>

60
00:06:02.570 --> 00:06:06.970
<i>No, there's something I must do 
as long as I'm wearing this ring.</i>

61
00:06:06.970 --> 00:06:10.970
<i>I'll become a fine husband for Honjoji-san!</i>

62
00:06:10.970 --> 00:06:13.480
Number withheld

63
00:06:10.970 --> 00:06:13.480
Slide to answer

64
00:06:14.580 --> 00:06:16.110
Yes, hello?

65
00:06:16.110 --> 00:06:17.950
<i>I know.</i>

66
00:06:18.730 --> 00:06:24.610
<i>Your supposed marriage with 
Honjoji Rika-san. It's a complete lie.</i>

67
00:06:24.610 --> 00:06:26.700
<i>I know all about it.</i>

68
00:06:26.700 --> 00:06:28.220
Uh, h-hey...

69
00:06:28.220 --> 00:06:31.620
<i>I'll send you both to Alaska!</i>

70
00:06:33.790 --> 00:06:34.750
<i>What?</i>

71
00:06:34.750 --> 00:06:37.250
Number withheld
 Call ended

72
00:06:35.110 --> 00:06:36.750
<i>What is this?</i>

73
00:06:37.250 --> 00:06:39.130
JTC Tourist
 JTC Travel

74
00:06:37.250 --> 00:06:39.130
Go to Hawaii!!

75
00:06:39.490 --> 00:06:40.750
A threatening call?

76
00:06:40.750 --> 00:06:43.590
I'm not sure if it was a threat or not.

77
00:06:43.590 --> 00:06:45.620
Do you know who it was from?

78
00:06:45.620 --> 00:06:47.150
I couldn't tell.

79
00:06:47.150 --> 00:06:49.010
The voice sounded synthesized.

80
00:06:49.010 --> 00:06:51.340
I'm not even sure of their gender.

81
00:06:51.340 --> 00:06:53.520
They know about Alaska.

82
00:06:53.990 --> 00:06:58.380
That means whoever made 
the call must work here?!

83
00:06:59.270 --> 00:07:00.860
Excuse me.

84
00:07:00.860 --> 00:07:03.360
Ohara-san, do you have a minute?

85
00:07:03.360 --> 00:07:06.150
G-G-Gonda?! What is it?

86
00:07:07.110 --> 00:07:08.240
Well...

87
00:07:08.580 --> 00:07:11.700
Would you mind if I came over tonight?

88
00:07:11.700 --> 00:07:13.840
To my place? What for?

89
00:07:13.840 --> 00:07:16.410
I just want to discuss something.

90
00:07:16.410 --> 00:07:20.130
<i>What's going on here? 
He's never done anything like this.</i>

91
00:07:20.400 --> 00:07:22.810
<i>I-It's too suspicious.</i>

92
00:07:22.810 --> 00:07:25.260
What do you think? Can I come over?

93
00:07:28.260 --> 00:07:29.950
Sure, by all means!

94
00:07:29.950 --> 00:07:31.740
We'd love to have you, Gonda-san.

95
00:07:31.740 --> 00:07:33.370
Huh? You too, Honjoji-san?

96
00:07:33.370 --> 00:07:36.020
Of course, I'll come over too.

97
00:07:36.020 --> 00:07:39.580
Look at you lovebirds. 
I wouldn't be intruding?

98
00:07:39.580 --> 00:07:41.120
Not at all, not at all.

99
00:07:41.120 --> 00:07:42.630
Thanks a lot!

100
00:07:42.630 --> 00:07:43.940
See you tonight!

101
00:07:45.530 --> 00:07:47.510
I'm sorry about this.

102
00:07:47.510 --> 00:07:49.050
M-Me too.

103
00:07:53.580 --> 00:07:56.220
<i>What is Gonda up to?</i>

104
00:07:56.220 --> 00:07:58.620
<i>Is Gonda-kun the one who made that call?</i>

105
00:07:59.130 --> 00:08:01.340
<i>We have to keep him from finding out!</i>

106
00:08:03.710 --> 00:08:07.840
Kama, listen. This is important.

107
00:08:08.120 --> 00:08:11.320
Some of my coworkers are coming over here.

108
00:08:11.320 --> 00:08:14.700
I know it's probably inconvenient for you, 
but please bear with me.

109
00:08:15.100 --> 00:08:18.270
Please, Kama! This is so important!

110
00:08:18.270 --> 00:08:20.440
My future and yours are riding on it.

111
00:08:20.730 --> 00:08:22.160
I'll make it up to you!

112
00:08:22.160 --> 00:08:25.120
I'll put Nyaru on your food for a month!

113
00:08:25.820 --> 00:08:28.570
Nyaru Gourmet
 Variety Pack

114
00:08:25.820 --> 00:08:28.570
I'll also stop sniffing you!

115
00:08:42.040 --> 00:08:44.500
Did your cat give his consent?

116
00:08:44.500 --> 00:08:45.730
Well...

117
00:08:45.730 --> 00:08:49.930
"Whatever. I'll put up with it 
for about an hour."

118
00:08:49.930 --> 00:08:52.000
That's the look he gave me.

119
00:08:52.000 --> 00:08:53.140
Aha.

120
00:08:54.110 --> 00:08:56.250
<i>So, this is Ohara-kun's apartment.</i>

121
00:08:56.250 --> 00:08:57.390
Here.

122
00:08:57.760 --> 00:08:59.030
You can use these slippers.

123
00:08:59.030 --> 00:09:00.520
Oh, don't make a fuss.

124
00:09:00.520 --> 00:09:02.190
They're yours to use.

125
00:09:03.080 --> 00:09:06.190
I went and bought some camouflage supplies.

126
00:09:06.190 --> 00:09:07.830
Camouflage?

127
00:09:07.830 --> 00:09:10.030
Items couples would be likely to use.

128
00:09:10.030 --> 00:09:14.090
I thought we'd use these to change this 
into a couple's apartment.

129
00:09:14.090 --> 00:09:15.780
W-Wow.

130
00:09:15.780 --> 00:09:17.170
Let's hurry.

131
00:09:17.840 --> 00:09:19.910
This is a checklist of items.

132
00:09:18.370 --> 00:09:19.910
Item Checklist

133
00:09:20.180 --> 00:09:22.630
Please arrange them as you see fit.

134
00:09:23.040 --> 00:09:26.920
Operation Love Nest

135
00:09:23.350 --> 00:09:25.090
<i>"Operation Love Nest"?!</i>

136
00:09:25.090 --> 00:09:26.920
<i>Honjoji-san doesn't mess around.</i>

137
00:09:26.920 --> 00:09:28.670
A doorplate for the entrance!

138
00:09:29.020 --> 00:09:32.180
Matching toothbrushes 
and cups at the sink, check!

139
00:09:32.660 --> 00:09:34.770
I placed the paired cushions on the bed.

140
00:09:34.770 --> 00:09:37.410
Got it. Where's your cat?

141
00:09:37.410 --> 00:09:39.260
He's in the adjoining room.

142
00:09:40.290 --> 00:09:41.920
That's where he spends most of his time.

143
00:09:41.920 --> 00:09:43.230
I see.

144
00:09:43.230 --> 00:09:47.360
Profile List

145
00:09:43.230 --> 00:09:47.360
Our first meeting
 When Ohara-kun was 22 and Honjoji was 24, 
we met while in Singapore for rookie training. 
At the time, we each got a passing impression
 that the other was optimistic about the job.
 First date
 On the anniversary of our first meeting
 (Saturday 10/12) we went on a date to
 Yokohama Space Land. Ohara-kun won a
 pig plushie from a UFO catcher, and we still
 have it on display.
How we refer to each other
 It's still "Ohara-kun" and "Honjoji-san," 
but we're working toward switching to 
"Takuya-kun" and "Rika-san."
 Favorite type of pancake
 Honjoji: banana 
Ohara: strawberry and hazelnut

146
00:09:44.100 --> 00:09:49.780
We first met during rookie training, 
and that was in...

147
00:09:49.780 --> 00:09:51.120
Singapore.

148
00:09:51.120 --> 00:09:56.480
My favorite kind of pancake is banana, 
and yours is strawberry and hazelnut.

149
00:09:56.480 --> 00:09:59.530
We're planning to honeymoon 
in Tahiti or the Maldives.

150
00:09:59.530 --> 00:10:01.520
Profile confirmation, done.

151
00:10:01.520 --> 00:10:02.750
Agreed.

152
00:10:03.080 --> 00:10:05.480
Next are photos to decorate the apartment.

153
00:10:05.480 --> 00:10:07.840
I collected reference images 
from the internet.

154
00:10:07.840 --> 00:10:09.630
W-Wow!

155
00:10:12.420 --> 00:10:13.390
Well...

156
00:10:13.390 --> 00:10:14.760
I think that's good.

157
00:10:15.980 --> 00:10:16.970
You know,

158
00:10:16.970 --> 00:10:19.460
this is like the day before an event.

159
00:10:19.460 --> 00:10:20.980
That it is.

160
00:10:20.980 --> 00:10:23.580
Like a cultural festival 
from our school days.

161
00:10:23.580 --> 00:10:26.440
Is this what your cultural 
festivals were like?

162
00:10:26.980 --> 00:10:31.180
Well, I was always a tree in a stage play.

163
00:10:31.180 --> 00:10:33.870
It was more less like that for me too.

164
00:10:33.870 --> 00:10:36.350
It's easy to really get into the tree role.

165
00:10:36.350 --> 00:10:39.870
And it has so much depth once you do.

166
00:10:40.120 --> 00:10:42.080
So, preparations are complete.

167
00:10:42.080 --> 00:10:44.350
He can show up anytime!

168
00:10:44.810 --> 00:10:46.120
There he is!

169
00:10:46.780 --> 00:10:48.150
Hello!

170
00:10:48.150 --> 00:10:49.500
Welcome!

171
00:10:49.500 --> 00:10:51.440
Hi, Ohara-san!

172
00:10:51.440 --> 00:10:52.760
We're here too.

173
00:10:53.510 --> 00:10:55.060
<i>Three of them?</i>

174
00:10:57.140 --> 00:10:58.890
Okay, one more time.

175
00:10:59.140 --> 00:11:01.260
Congrats on getting engaged!

176
00:11:01.770 --> 00:11:04.560
I bought lots of drinks!

177
00:11:04.560 --> 00:11:06.270
Th-Thanks.

178
00:11:06.270 --> 00:11:08.900
<i>This is going to run long, Honjoji-san.</i>

179
00:11:08.900 --> 00:11:11.380
<i>Isn't this a state of emergency?</i>

180
00:11:11.380 --> 00:11:13.760
<i>It's okay. Just do as we practiced.</i>

181
00:11:15.000 --> 00:11:18.410
So, Gonda. What did you 
want to discuss today?

182
00:11:18.410 --> 00:11:20.960
Yeah, about that, Ohara-san.

183
00:11:24.410 --> 00:11:27.480
Please teach me how to get hitched!

184
00:11:27.480 --> 00:11:28.420
Huh?

185
00:11:28.420 --> 00:11:32.750
I want to get married too, 
but it's not going well at all.

186
00:11:32.750 --> 00:11:35.780
I thought I'd ask you for some pointers.

187
00:11:36.430 --> 00:11:39.210
Gonda is on seven online dating apps.

188
00:11:39.210 --> 00:11:41.120
You use that many of them?!

189
00:11:41.120 --> 00:11:43.340
Cut that out, Keisuke-san!

190
00:11:43.340 --> 00:11:45.100
Komiya-chan heard you!

191
00:11:45.100 --> 00:11:47.350
Give up on those apps.

192
00:11:45.850 --> 00:11:47.350
<i>What's happening here?</i>

193
00:11:47.660 --> 00:11:49.100
Oh, date photos.

194
00:11:49.100 --> 00:11:50.570
That's in Yokohama.

195
00:11:50.570 --> 00:11:52.880
How long have you been dating?

196
00:11:52.880 --> 00:11:54.590
Since rookie training.

197
00:11:54.590 --> 00:11:57.200
Everyone, help yourself to snacks!

198
00:11:57.200 --> 00:11:58.710
Honjoji-san is...

199
00:11:58.710 --> 00:11:59.710
...smiling!

200
00:11:59.710 --> 00:12:02.700
It's like she's filled with happiness!

201
00:12:02.700 --> 00:12:05.040
This'll be one legendary marriage.

202
00:12:05.040 --> 00:12:08.440
I still can't believe no one 
at work realized.

203
00:12:08.440 --> 00:12:10.280
I-I need to use the restroom.

204
00:12:10.630 --> 00:12:12.820
Learn while you're here, Gonda.

205
00:12:12.820 --> 00:12:15.900
I'm ready for my training, Master!

206
00:12:16.430 --> 00:12:18.160
I wish someone would teach me.

207
00:12:20.020 --> 00:12:23.040
I'm not sure what I should say.

208
00:12:23.760 --> 00:12:28.140
Suddenly I'm surrounded by everyone, 
getting peppered with questions.

209
00:12:28.640 --> 00:12:31.310
Is marriage that great?

210
00:12:31.780 --> 00:12:37.230
I said I would get married, and 
I put on a ring, but that's all.

211
00:12:37.900 --> 00:12:40.970
I haven't changed at all.

212
00:12:42.250 --> 00:12:43.470
Is marriage...

213
00:12:44.720 --> 00:12:47.460
Is marriage really that great?

214
00:12:48.720 --> 00:12:50.500
It <i>is</i> amazing!

215
00:12:50.500 --> 00:12:53.640
It sounds snide when you 
talk like that, Ohara-san!

216
00:12:53.640 --> 00:12:55.800
You should just be happy about it!

217
00:12:55.800 --> 00:12:57.230
That's right!

218
00:12:57.230 --> 00:12:58.860
They speak the truth.

219
00:13:02.650 --> 00:13:04.150
Thanks for having us.

220
00:13:04.150 --> 00:13:06.620
Thank you for today.

221
00:13:06.620 --> 00:13:07.980
See you.

222
00:13:07.980 --> 00:13:09.420
Ohara-san.

223
00:13:11.170 --> 00:13:12.560
Between you and me.

224
00:13:12.560 --> 00:13:13.900
Wh-What?

225
00:13:14.360 --> 00:13:17.780
I've actually got my eye on Komiya-chan.

226
00:13:17.780 --> 00:13:18.720
What?

227
00:13:18.720 --> 00:13:22.080
I'd be happy for any support you can offer!

228
00:13:25.490 --> 00:13:27.870
Let's go get some ramen, Gonda.

229
00:13:27.870 --> 00:13:29.090
Ow, ow, ow.

230
00:13:29.090 --> 00:13:30.870
Marriage would be great.

231
00:13:30.870 --> 00:13:35.440
You mean Gonda really only 
came over to get some advice?

232
00:13:36.010 --> 00:13:39.010
Then who was it that made that call?

233
00:13:40.900 --> 00:13:42.380
I'm home.

234
00:13:42.380 --> 00:13:43.800
Welcome back.

235
00:13:43.800 --> 00:13:45.640
Th-Thanks...

236
00:13:45.640 --> 00:13:48.320
<i>I came back through the door on auto-pilot.</i>

237
00:13:51.080 --> 00:13:54.130
I will never play host again.

238
00:13:54.130 --> 00:13:55.640
Agreed.

239
00:13:57.050 --> 00:13:59.830
I feel the same way as you, Ohara-kun.

240
00:13:59.830 --> 00:14:04.440
I don't understand why everyone celebrates 
so much because we're getting married.

241
00:14:04.810 --> 00:14:06.780
It's not like it's their marriage.

242
00:14:07.200 --> 00:14:10.310
Apparently, it looks like 
we're glowing to all of them.

243
00:14:11.040 --> 00:14:12.290
Like lights.

244
00:14:12.290 --> 00:14:17.130
I bet it's the ones who can see 
that light who will get married.

245
00:14:17.960 --> 00:14:21.380
I can't see it at all.

246
00:14:22.150 --> 00:14:24.560
And I probably won't, down the road.

247
00:14:24.980 --> 00:14:27.650
That's not the sort of life I'm leading.

248
00:14:32.190 --> 00:14:37.730
Uh, but... I have a feeling you can 
see the light without getting married.

249
00:14:38.100 --> 00:14:44.240
I have Kama, and when I come home from work, 
and he and I eat and watch TV,

250
00:14:44.560 --> 00:14:46.520
I feel like I'm glowing then.

251
00:14:46.520 --> 00:14:48.680
That's what glowing is?

252
00:14:48.680 --> 00:14:51.240
It might be something a little different.

253
00:14:51.980 --> 00:14:53.740
But it's enough for me.

254
00:14:54.900 --> 00:14:57.830
Honjoji-san, do you have anything like that?

255
00:14:57.830 --> 00:15:02.130
I think so. When I come home 
and look at maps.

256
00:15:02.130 --> 00:15:04.000
Do you enjoy that?

257
00:15:04.000 --> 00:15:06.990
I do! Maps are so interesting!

258
00:15:06.990 --> 00:15:10.040
Places like Eboshi Island in Fukushima 
are a page of nothing but ocean,

259
00:15:10.040 --> 00:15:12.590
and one little island all by itself! Also—

260
00:15:12.590 --> 00:15:14.770
That would be glowing.

261
00:15:15.870 --> 00:15:19.560
I-I'm not... glowing at all.

262
00:15:26.860 --> 00:15:30.370
W-Well, I'd best be going.

263
00:15:30.740 --> 00:15:34.610
R-Right. See you tomorrow.

264
00:15:36.770 --> 00:15:39.450
<i>My chest feels tight.</i>

265
00:15:39.450 --> 00:15:42.340
<i>It's because I'm not 
used to being around a man.</i>

266
00:15:42.700 --> 00:15:45.090
<i>It'll be no big deal, soon enough.</i>

267
00:15:45.090 --> 00:15:47.110
<i>It's not like I'm in junior high.</i>

268
00:15:48.300 --> 00:15:51.630
<i>Honjoji-san was wonderful today.</i>

269
00:15:52.100 --> 00:15:54.420
<i>Whoa, don't get all weird now.</i>

270
00:15:54.420 --> 00:15:56.830
<i>We're just working together on this.</i>

271
00:15:58.760 --> 00:16:00.940
<i>I can't get the wrong idea.</i>

272
00:16:10.950 --> 00:16:13.160
JTC Tourist
 JTC Travel

273
00:16:13.160 --> 00:16:15.440
The new package is done.

274
00:16:13.160 --> 00:16:18.420
From "When are we going?" 
to "Let's go now."
 It's time for travel.

275
00:16:15.920 --> 00:16:18.110
<i>Now I hope the tickets sell well.</i>

276
00:16:18.420 --> 00:16:20.790
<i>I'm quite confident in this one.</i>

277
00:16:21.130 --> 00:16:23.290
<i>"The Hawaii not everyone knows."</i>

278
00:16:23.290 --> 00:16:28.300
351 days until the
 Anchorage Branch opens

279
00:16:23.590 --> 00:16:28.300
<i>Two weeks after the engagement announcement, 
the mood at work has finally calmed down.</i>

280
00:16:28.850 --> 00:16:33.890
<i>I am concerned about that phone call 
Ohara-kun got, but there's been no follow-up.</i>

281
00:16:34.640 --> 00:16:36.310
<i>In any case, I'm surviving!</i>

282
00:16:36.310 --> 00:16:38.360
<i>I'll believe in myself and keep at it!</i>

283
00:16:38.360 --> 00:16:42.230
Hey, excuse me. Is this JTC?

284
00:16:42.230 --> 00:16:44.440
<i>A customer?! Damn!</i>

285
00:16:44.440 --> 00:16:48.680
<i>It was careless of me to come out here. 
I'm bad at dealing with customers!</i>

286
00:16:48.680 --> 00:16:50.970
Welcome. Are you planning a trip?

287
00:16:50.970 --> 00:16:52.570
Ah, thanks.

288
00:16:52.570 --> 00:16:56.750
Please take a numbered ticket from here, 
and have a seat over there.

289
00:16:52.570 --> 00:16:58.830
Overseas Counter

290
00:16:52.570 --> 00:16:58.830
5 parties waiting 
to be served

291
00:16:56.750 --> 00:16:58.830
Ah, thanks.

292
00:16:59.630 --> 00:17:02.190
<i>This guy looks angry.</i>

293
00:17:02.190 --> 00:17:04.900
<i>I hadn't spoken to a customer in a long time.</i>

294
00:17:09.930 --> 00:17:14.580
Excuse me. No counter looks likely 
to open up, so I will help you.

295
00:17:14.580 --> 00:17:16.600
Ah, thanks.

296
00:17:19.620 --> 00:17:22.120
Where are you thinking of traveling?

297
00:17:22.120 --> 00:17:24.060
Well, here.

298
00:17:24.360 --> 00:17:26.320
My card.

299
00:17:24.390 --> 00:17:26.320
Ohara Cleaning
 CEO
 Ohara Koichi

300
00:17:27.750 --> 00:17:29.070
<i>Ohara?</i>

301
00:17:29.370 --> 00:17:33.240
My son Takuya is employed here.

302
00:17:33.240 --> 00:17:34.160
What?!

303
00:17:34.160 --> 00:17:37.290
Listen, between you and me.

304
00:17:37.290 --> 00:17:42.320
I happened to hear that my son 
is going to get married,

305
00:17:42.320 --> 00:17:45.500
but he hasn't said a word about it to me.

306
00:17:45.840 --> 00:17:48.760
<i>Ohara-kun's father?! What's he doing here?!</i>

307
00:17:49.190 --> 00:17:50.810
<i>Did Ohara-kun tell him?</i>

308
00:17:50.810 --> 00:17:52.270
<i>No, that can't be.</i>

309
00:17:52.270 --> 00:17:56.010
<i>How then? I wonder 
where his father heard it.</i>

310
00:17:56.010 --> 00:17:57.350
<i>I didn't...</i>

311
00:17:58.060 --> 00:18:01.450
<i>I didn't think about family-related stuff.</i>

312
00:18:01.450 --> 00:18:05.270
Miss, do you know anything about this?

313
00:18:05.270 --> 00:18:10.110
I-I'm afraid I do not.

314
00:18:13.200 --> 00:18:15.600
Well, if you'll pardon me.

315
00:18:16.530 --> 00:18:21.170
Uh, please don't let my son know I was here.

316
00:18:23.750 --> 00:18:27.270
Here, have one of my company's products.

317
00:18:30.550 --> 00:18:32.550
Ohara Cleaning Ltd. 
Desktop Calendar

318
00:18:30.550 --> 00:18:32.550
Many thanks

319
00:18:42.300 --> 00:18:44.280
<i>Ohara-kun's... not here!</i>

320
00:18:44.280 --> 00:18:46.130
<i>I wanted to talk to him, too!</i>

321
00:18:48.400 --> 00:18:50.400
Honjoji

322
00:18:48.400 --> 00:18:50.400
Ohara

323
00:18:48.400 --> 00:18:50.400
Itsuki

324
00:18:48.400 --> 00:18:50.400
Out of office

325
00:18:48.400 --> 00:18:50.400
He's out of the office.

326
00:18:50.400 --> 00:18:53.210
<i>I ended up lying to his father.</i>

327
00:18:53.210 --> 00:18:55.460
<i>Even though the whole thing's my idea.</i>

328
00:18:55.460 --> 00:18:58.910
<i>Things just escalated so rapidly.</i>

329
00:18:56.660 --> 00:18:58.910
Higashi, Kumamoto, Kumamoto Prefecture
Ohara Cleaning Ltd.

330
00:18:59.230 --> 00:19:02.130
<i>Ohara-kun's from Kumamoto Prefecture!</i>

331
00:19:02.130 --> 00:19:04.290
<i>His father came all the way here?!</i>

332
00:19:04.290 --> 00:19:07.310
<i>I-I feel so bad about this.</i>

333
00:19:07.310 --> 00:19:09.660
<i>Is it okay to just let him leave?</i>

334
00:19:09.660 --> 00:19:11.710
<i>No, that's no way to behave!</i>

335
00:19:11.710 --> 00:19:13.880
<i>I'll go tell him everything!</i>

336
00:19:13.880 --> 00:19:16.020
<i>That we aren't really getting married!</i>

337
00:19:14.670 --> 00:19:16.680
Ohara Cleaning Ltd. 
Desktop Calendar

338
00:19:14.670 --> 00:19:16.680
Many thanks

339
00:19:19.270 --> 00:19:20.150
<i>He's still here!</i>

340
00:19:20.150 --> 00:19:21.890
<i>He and his son both have a slouch!</i>

341
00:19:23.430 --> 00:19:24.640
I can't put up with this.

342
00:19:26.270 --> 00:19:30.470
Takuya's sure to bring ruin 
to the Ohara family.

343
00:19:34.030 --> 00:19:35.310
E-Excuse me!

344
00:19:35.860 --> 00:19:39.620
Um, Ohara-kun is currently out.

345
00:19:39.620 --> 00:19:41.620
I'll give him a call.

346
00:19:41.620 --> 00:19:44.140
No need to trouble yourself.

347
00:19:44.140 --> 00:19:47.420
It's no problem. 
Please come wait over this way.

348
00:19:48.630 --> 00:19:50.500
<i>I've got to get away from the office.</i>

349
00:19:49.670 --> 00:19:52.420
Today

350
00:19:49.670 --> 00:19:52.420
Ohara-kun, I'm with your father right now. 
We'll be waiting at Z Coffee.

351
00:19:52.420 --> 00:19:55.420
Z Coffee

352
00:19:55.420 --> 00:19:58.430
I'm glad it all worked out all right.

353
00:20:01.790 --> 00:20:06.650
<i>I want to talk to him, but what do I say 
when things are this tense?</i>

354
00:20:07.340 --> 00:20:11.500
Um, earlier you mentioned 
Ohara-kun ruining your family.

355
00:20:11.870 --> 00:20:13.820
What does that mean?

356
00:20:16.790 --> 00:20:21.230
It's problematic if he arbitrarily goes and 
decides on something important like marriage.

357
00:20:21.230 --> 00:20:24.520
Marriages require a range of preparations.

358
00:20:26.180 --> 00:20:28.400
That includes preparing the dolls.

359
00:20:28.400 --> 00:20:29.290
Dolls?

360
00:20:29.640 --> 00:20:32.540
Takasago dolls, on display during 
the betrothal gift exchange.

361
00:20:32.540 --> 00:20:34.810
Those are essential.

362
00:20:34.810 --> 00:20:39.580
Then there are the decorative knots, the red 
sea bream served whole, and kimono and sake.

363
00:20:39.580 --> 00:20:42.680
Much has to happen, 
starting with the gift exchange.

364
00:20:42.680 --> 00:20:45.090
<i>Exchanging betrothal gifts.</i>

365
00:20:45.090 --> 00:20:48.060
<i>I hadn't planned to take it that far, 
so it never crossed my mind.</i>

366
00:20:48.060 --> 00:20:51.390
I also have to notify the group.

367
00:20:51.390 --> 00:20:52.310
Group?

368
00:20:52.310 --> 00:20:54.270
The local assembly.

369
00:20:54.270 --> 00:20:59.320
We live out in the country in Aso, so 
there are a number of things to do locally.

370
00:20:59.650 --> 00:21:01.700
Bonds run deep out there,

371
00:21:01.700 --> 00:21:06.860
so when a wedding happens, 
we invite neighbors and coworkers.

372
00:21:06.860 --> 00:21:09.540
It will mean two hundred people, all told.

373
00:21:09.540 --> 00:21:11.770
<i>T-Two hundred?!</i>

374
00:21:13.110 --> 00:21:16.270
And we reserve a hot spring resort.

375
00:21:16.270 --> 00:21:19.590
The festivities go all day 
and late into the night.

376
00:21:19.590 --> 00:21:21.340
<i>For that long?</i>

377
00:21:21.340 --> 00:21:25.350
During this, we do dances like 
the Ushibuka Haiya.

378
00:21:25.350 --> 00:21:28.530
<i>U-Ushibuka Haiya? 
What kind of dance is that?</i>

379
00:21:28.530 --> 00:21:32.310
The local firefighters 
put on quite a good show.

380
00:21:32.310 --> 00:21:34.270
<i>Why are firefighters at a wedding?!</i>

381
00:21:34.270 --> 00:21:36.860
Then finally, we toss 
the bride into the air.

382
00:21:36.860 --> 00:21:37.330
<i>Toss...?</i>

383
00:21:37.330 --> 00:21:38.080
Heave ho!

384
00:21:38.080 --> 00:21:39.620
<i>What?!</i>

385
00:21:41.310 --> 00:21:43.770
Wh-What a big event.

386
00:21:43.770 --> 00:21:46.300
That's an Aso-style wedding.

387
00:21:46.300 --> 00:21:50.830
Takuya is my eldest son. 
If his wedding isn't done properly,

388
00:21:50.830 --> 00:21:53.210
our family will lose face!

389
00:21:55.960 --> 00:21:57.210
Understood. Thank you.

390
00:21:55.960 --> 00:21:57.210
Today

391
00:21:55.960 --> 00:21:57.210
Ohara-kun, I'm with your father right now. 
We'll be waiting at Z Coffee.

392
00:21:56.090 --> 00:21:57.210
Higashi, Kumamoto, Kumamoto Prefecture
Ohara Cleaning Ltd.

393
00:21:57.210 --> 00:21:59.190
<i>Wh-Why?</i>

394
00:21:59.190 --> 00:22:01.720
<i>Honjoji-san and Dad are together?!</i>

395
00:22:01.720 --> 00:22:03.970
Today

396
00:22:01.720 --> 00:22:03.970
Ohara-kun, I'm with your father right now. 
We'll be waiting at Z Coffee.

397
00:22:02.740 --> 00:22:03.970
<i>We're in trouble.</i>

